<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-02T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="742" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/255: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-02T17:00:00-05:00">November 2, 1940—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>372. From the Ambassador. Your telegram No. 561, November 1, 3 p.m.
                            Please tell Aranha I spoke this afternoon on the subject in which he is
                            interested to the British Chargé d’Affaires here who promised to
                            telegraph at once about the matter to his government. [Caffery.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>